New Records: Giannis Antetokounmpo set a new record with his 26th-straight game scoring at least 20 or more points on 50 percent shooting or better
Key Match Events: A 20-0 rally in the final six and a half minutes
Damian Lillard missed a potential game-winning three-pointer
Ziaire Williams made two free throws to tie the score
A creative sideline out-of-bounds play led to a good look for Lillard
Pre-Game Insights: The Bucks knew the Nets would play physical defense and force turnovers
Coach Doc Rivers emphasized the need for better focus and execution
Post-Match Reflections: Coach Doc Rivers expressed frustration with the team's performance
Giannis Antetokounmpo emphasized the need for better mental focus and teamwork
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks committed 14 turnovers, leading to 27 points for the Nets
This was the third time the Nets had beaten the Bucks this season
